MASTER SERVICE AGREEMENT
Acme Cloud Analytics, Inc. ("Vendor") and Customer

Effective Date: January 1, 2025

1. SERVICES
Vendor will provide cloud-based data analytics services as described in the applicable Order Form.

2. DATA PROCESSING
Vendor may process Customer data on infrastructure located in any jurisdiction, including regions outside
the European Economic Area, without prior notice to Customer. Vendor retains the right to use
aggregated, anonymized Customer data for product improvement and benchmarking purposes. Data
deletion upon contract termination will occur within 180 days of written request.

3. CONFIDENTIALITY
Each party agrees to maintain the confidentiality of the other party's Confidential Information. However,
Vendor's obligations shall not apply to information that Vendor independently develops or receives from
third parties without restriction.

4. INDEMNIFICATION
Customer shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Vendor and its affiliates from and against any
and all claims, damages, losses, and expenses arising from: (a) Customer's use of the Services;
(b) Customer's breach of this Agreement; or (c) any third-party claims arising from Customer Data.
Vendor's liability to Customer shall not exceed the fees paid in the three (3) months preceding the claim.

5. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY
IN NO EVENT SHALL VENDOR BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, EXEMPLARY, OR
CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES. VENDOR'S TOTAL AGGREGATE LIABILITY SHALL NOT EXCEED THREE (3)
MONTHS OF FEES PAID. THIS LIMITATION APPLIES REGARDLESS OF THE THEORY OF LIABILITY.

6. AUTO-RENEWAL AND TERMINATION
This Agreement automatically renews for successive one-year terms unless either party provides
written notice of non-renewal no later than fifteen (15) days before the end of the then-current term.
Vendor may terminate this Agreement or suspend Services immediately upon notice if Customer
breaches any payment obligation or violates Vendor's Acceptable Use Policy.

7. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY
All improvements, modifications, or derivative works created by Vendor in connection with the Services,
even if based on Customer feedback or requirements, shall be owned exclusively by Vendor. Customer
grants Vendor a perpetual, irrevocable license to use Customer Data in anonymized form.

8. GOVERNING LAW AND DISPUTE RESOLUTION
This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of the State of Delaware. Any dispute shall be resolved
by binding arbitration in Wilmington, Delaware, under AAA Commercial Arbitration Rules. Customer
waives any right to a jury trial and agrees not to bring class action claims against Vendor.

9. SUBPROCESSORS
Vendor may engage subprocessors without prior written consent of Customer. Vendor will maintain a
list of subprocessors on its website and update it from time to time without direct notification.

10. SECURITY
Vendor agrees to implement "commercially reasonable" security measures appropriate to the nature
of the data processed. Vendor will notify Customer of security incidents affecting Customer Data
within 72 hours of Vendor becoming aware of the breach.

